This paper deals with the optimization of trajectories for quadruped robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed constraints are related to the dynamics of the robot, which suggests the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of a nonlinear non-convex optimization problem, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The proposed model for leg collision avoidance could also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) since it involves sensing and reacting to the environment.
